---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout
  title="How Tall is 6 Feet in Centimetres?"
  description="Convert 6 feet to centimetres and understand height conversions between imperial and metric systems."
  keywords="6 feet in cm, feet to cm, height conversion, imperial to metric height, how tall is 6 feet"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Length</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="How Tall is 6 Feet in Centimetres?" />

      <!-- Article Meta -->
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-06">June 6, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Lead Paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Height conversions come up constantly in international contexts — dating profiles, medical records, sports statistics. Here is the definitive answer and the maths behind it.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: The Answer -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Answer</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-center text-xl font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">
          6 feet = 182.88 cm
        </p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">
          1 foot = 30.48 cm | 1 inch = 2.54 cm
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: The Formula -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How to Convert Feet to Centimetres</h2>
      <p>The conversion is straightforward:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Convert feet to inches (multiply by 12)</li>
        <li>Add any extra inches</li>
        <li>Multiply total inches by 2.54</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> 6 feet 0 inches → 72 inches × 2.54 = <strong>182.88 cm</strong></p>

      <!-- Section: Common Heights -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Height Conversions</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Feet & Inches</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Centimetres</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">5'4"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">162.6 cm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">5'6"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">167.6 cm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">5'8"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">172.7 cm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">5'10"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">177.8 cm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">6'0"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">182.9 cm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">6'2"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">188.0 cm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">6'4"</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">193.0 cm</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Context -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Is 6 Feet Tall?</h2>
      <p>In most countries, 6 feet (182.9 cm) is considered above average height:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Global average male height:</strong> ~5'7" (171 cm)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>US average male:</strong> 5'9" (175.3 cm)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Netherlands average male:</strong> 5'11.5" (182 cm) — the world's tallest</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>So at 6 feet, you are taller than roughly 85% of men worldwide.</p>

      <!-- Section: Quick Mental Conversion -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Quick Mental Trick</h2>
      <p>For a rough feet-to-cm conversion: multiply feet by 30 and add a bit. This gets you within 2%:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>5 feet × 30 = 150 cm (actual: 152.4)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>6 feet × 30 = 180 cm (actual: 182.9)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>6.5 feet × 30 = 195 cm (actual: 198.1)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Converter CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">
            🔗 Try our free length converter
          </p>
          <a
            href="/convert/length"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Open Converter →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Blog -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">
          ← Back to all articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
